6. Integration Protocol for New Theories

When adding new physics field Φ:
text

1. Identify the interaction term: L_Φ = Φ O[Standard]
2. Replace: L_Φ → L_Φ × F(X^2)
   where F(X^2) = exp[-(X_μ X^μ)/Λ^2]
3. Λ = M_Pl × (m_S/M_Pl)^{1/2} ≈ 10^8 GeV
4. Result: New physics turns off where X is large (high baryon density)

Example: For a new scalar force:
Lnew=−12(∂Φ)2−12mΦ2Φ2+gΦJDM
Lnew​=−21​(∂Φ)2−21​mΦ2​Φ2+gΦJDM​

Becomes:
Lnew=−12(∂Φ)2−12mΦ2Φ2+gΦJDM×exp⁡[−XμXμΛ2]
Lnew​=−21​(∂Φ)2−21​mΦ2​Φ2+gΦJDM​×exp[−Λ2Xμ​Xμ​]
